    sec_material: `Atlanta's intown bungalow belt -- Virginia-Highland, Inman Park, Grant Park, Candler Park, and Cabbagetown -- runs original 1920s-1940s wood lap siding on approximately 25-35% of the housing stock, much of it heart pine or cypress milled from Georgia Piedmont forests. The continuing Buckhead and Brookhaven tear-down-and-rebuild cycle has made James Hardie fiber cement the default specification on new infill construction. Suburban Gwinnett, Forsyth, and Henry counties are dominated by brick veneer at 40-50% of the metro's total residential footprint. Vinyl is prohibited outright by AUDC in all 20+ designated historic districts and by HOA covenant in Buckhead, Morningside, and Druid Hills.`,
